During the [[Kemmu Restoration]] in [[Kemmu (era)|Kemmu]] 2 (1335), the fourth lord {{ill|Ōi Chikayuki|ja|大井朝行|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi Chikayuki|qq=}} supported the {{ill|Ashikaga clan|ja|足利氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashikaga clan|qq=}}, joining the Northern Court. He clashed with the Southern Court forces, including {{ill|Kutsuna Shigekiyo|ja|忽那重清|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kutsuna Shigekiyo|qq=}}, who were advancing toward [[Kamakura]] along the Eastern Mountain Road. Despite several days of fierce resistance, the castle eventually fell, as recorded in documents like ''Battle of Ōi Manor'' and ''Kutsuna Papers''.
The castle was later rebuilt. The fifth lord, {{ill|Ōi Mitsusaka|ja|大井光栄|lt=Ōi Mitsunaga (Mitsusaka)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi Mitsusaka|qq=}}, served as Deputy Governor of Shinano Province. His son, the sixth lord {{ill|Ōi Mitsunori|ja|大井光矩|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi Mitsunori|qq=}}, mediated during the [[Ōtō Rebellion]] in [[Ōei]] 7 (1400), aiding the defeated {{ill|Ogasawara Nagahide|ja|小笠原長秀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ogasawara Nagahide|qq=}}.
